I see. The main goal is to analyze a time-series of images showing the expression of a fluorescent protein in cells, aiming to quantify the co-localization between this protein and a specific organelle over time. The signal is weak and noisy, so the pipeline needs to address this issue effectively.

First, the pipeline will apply denoising filters to the images. This step is crucial because it helps reduce noise, which is a common issue when dealing with weak and noisy signals. By doing this, the pipeline can provide more accurate data for further analysis.

